&lt;p&gt;Can I use the following jQuery code to perform file upload using POST method of an ajax request ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-js s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-javascript&quot;&gt;$.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;ajax&lt;/span&gt;({
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;POST&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;timeout&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-number&quot;&gt;50000&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;url&lt;/span&gt;: url,
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;: dataString,
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;success&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-params&quot;&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;alert&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;success&apos;&lt;/span&gt;);
        &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-literal&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;;
    }
});
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If it is possible, do I need to fill &lt;code&gt;data&lt;/code&gt; part? Is it the correct way? I only POST the file to the server side.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have been googling around, but what I found was a plugin while in my plan I do not want to use it. At least for the moment.&lt;/p&gt;
